[2] Outbreak summaries
- Fri 17 May 2019 CIDRAP news scan
[CIDRAP (Center for Infectious Disease research and Policy) abridged, edited]
http://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2019/05/news-scan-may-17-2019

The Democratic Republic of the Congo's (DRC's) ministry of health confirmed 17 new cases of Ebola today [17 May 2019] and 16 more deaths in the ongoing outbreak in North Kivu and Ituri provinces.

The new cases raise the outbreak total to 1777 cases, including 1177 deaths. A total of 333 suspected cases are still under investigation. 9 of the 16 deaths occurred in the community, which raises the risk of further transmission.

Of the new cases, 5 originated in Butembo, 4 in Mabalako, 2 each in Katwa and Beni, and 1 case each in Vuhovi, Musienene, Biena, and Kalunguta.

Vaccination continues throughout the region. As of today, 118 029 people have been vaccinated with Merck's VSV-EBOV vaccine [119 652 vaccinated persons as of 18 May 2019 -- see item [1] above].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

