- Thu 16 May 2019. Aid group: More funds needed for Ebola safe burials in Congo
[Bradenton Herald, Associated Press (AP) report, abridged, edited]
https://www.bradenton.com/news/local/health-care/article230483814.html


An international aid organization says it only has enough funding to continue safe burials for Ebola victims in eastern Congo for 2 more weeks.

The International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies said [Thu 16 May 2019] that unless it gets more funding it won't be able to continue providing support to crews burying Ebola victims.

Each Ebola burial costs about USD 500 for, among other things, the protective gear for workers.

--
