- Fri 17 May 2019. New rebel attack in Beni, at least 10 dead
[Actualite; in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://actualite.cd/2019/05/17/rdc-nouvelle-attaque-rebelle-beni-au-moins-10-morts

At least 10 people, including 9 civilians and one soldier, died this morning [17 May 2019] in an attack attributed to Ugandan rebels of Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) in Kilhewa, a village at kilometer point 13 (PK13) on the Mbau-Kamango road in the territory from Beni (North Kivu).

The rebel assault was launched at 9 am, the attackers targeted the civilian population, the military intervened. The local civil society that adds this report adds that three people do not answer the call so far and one civilian is seriously injured.

"There are 9 civilians killed, including 5 women and 4 men, among them pygmies, a killed soldier, and a wounded civilian, 3 missing persons, and we are following the situation in the area. [The attack was] a surprise for all the communities that are in the area there.

--
