- Fri 17 May 2019. Effects on economy of Beni Butembo and Lubero
[Radio Okapi; in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2019/05/17/actualite/economie/rdc-ebola-affecte-leconomie-de-beni-butembo-et-lubero-selon-la-fec

The outbreak of Ebola haemorrhagic fever in Beni, Butembo, and Lubero (North Kivu) has negatively affected the economy in this region. According to the president of the local group of the Federation of Enterprises of the Congo (FEC), Polycarpe Ndivito, production and trade with some neighboring countries and the export of some products to Uganda and Kenya are slowing down as a result of this epidemic. He is talking about a loss of several million dollars since the declaration of this disease in the region.

Polycarpe Ndivito reports distrust of traders in rural areas: "The production itself has fallen sharply because people are suspicious, for example those who leave Butembo as a center to go to rural areas. They cannot get in easily because the (villagers) with whom they have to collaborate in rural areas are saying, 'People who come from Butembo have Ebola virus disease' and that affects production."

According to him, the marketing of local products, banana, tea, wood, cocoa, coffee, is also affected by the epidemic. Customers who had to leave Kampala (Uganda) or Kenya to buy these products no longer come for fear of the disease. This fear slows trade.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

